                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">ABS:</span> Dual-channel ABS with switchable off-road mode, offering more braking control on loose surfaces.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Suspension:</span> Fully adjustable WP Apex suspension on both front and rear, allowing riders to customize the suspension to match their preferred riding style.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <span class="font-weight-700">Tyres:</span> Dual-purpose tyres suited for both tarmac and gravel.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <h3 class="subheading">Comfort and Safety Enhancements</h3>
                <p>With enhanced ergonomics, the 390 Adventure offers a more upright riding posture and a taller seat height. The advanced suspension, coupled with improved ABS and traction control, provides safety and stability even on challenging terrains.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Mileage and Efficiency</h3>
                <p>Expected fuel efficiency is approximately 25-28 km/l, suitable for adventure riding without frequent fuel stops.</p>
                <h3 class="subheading">Market Competition</h3>
                <p>The KTM 390 Adventure will compete with models like the Royal Enfield Himalayan, BMW G 310 GS, and Honda CB500X, catering to adventure enthusiasts in India.</p>
